<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Debug Tools - NestJS Auth Demo</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha1/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container my-5">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-12">
                <h1 class="mb-4">Debug Tools</h1>
                <div class="alert alert-warning">
                    <strong>Warning:</strong> These debug tools should not be enabled in production environments as they expose sensitive data.
                </div>
                
                <div class="card mb-4">
                    <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
                        <h3 class="mb-0">Available Debug Tools</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <div class="list-group">
                            <a href="/debug/redis-session" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center">
                                <div>
                                    <h5 class="mb-1">Redis Session Debug</h5>
                                    <p class="mb-1">Inspect all Redis sessions, view session data, and examine session storage</p>
                                </div>
                                <span class="badge bg-primary rounded-pill">View</span>
                            </a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="card mb-4">
                    <div class="card-header bg-info text-white">
                        <h3 class="mb-0">Redis Troubleshooting</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5>If the Redis Session Debug tool isn't working correctly:</h5>
                        <ol>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Make sure Redis is running</strong>
                                <pre class="bg-light p-2 mt-1 mb-3">docker-compose up -d</pre>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Verify Redis is accessible</strong>
                                <pre class="bg-light p-2 mt-1 mb-3">docker ps | grep redis</pre>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Test Redis connection using our helper script</strong>
                                <pre class="bg-light p-2 mt-1 mb-3">npm run test:redis</pre>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Try connecting directly with redis-cli</strong>
                                <pre class="bg-light p-2 mt-1 mb-3">redis-cli -p 6380 ping</pre>
                                <p class="small text-muted">You should get "PONG" as a response if Redis is working</p>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                        
                        <div class="alert alert-info">
                            <strong>Note:</strong> The application will fall back to in-memory session storage if Redis is unavailable. 
                            However, the Redis Session Debug tool requires a working Redis connection.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="mt-4">
                    <a href="/" class="btn btn-outline-secondary">Back to Home</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html> 